The '''Citizens' List''' ({{lang-lb|Biergerlëscht}}, {{lang-fr|Liste des citoyens}}) is a [[Luxembourg]]ian [[political party]].  It was founded in the run-up to the [[Luxembourgish legislative election, 2009|2009 Chamber of Deputies election]] and [[European Parliament election, 2009 (Luxembourg)|European election]].  It ran in two [[Legislative circonscriptions (Luxembourg)|circonscriptions]]; in [[Circonscription Sud (Luxembourg)|Sud]], the list was to be headed by [[Aly Jaerling]], then an [[Independent (politician)|independent]] member of the [[Chamber of Deputies of Luxembourg|Chamber of Deputies]], whilst, in [[Circonscription Nord (Luxembourg)|Nord]], it was led by [[Jean Ersfeld]], formerly leader of the [[Free Party of Luxembourg]].<ref name="Gegen Rentenklau">{{cite news |first= |last= |title=Gegen Rentenklau |url=http://www.wort.lu/wort/web/letzebuerg/artikel/14276/gegen-rentenklau.php |publisher=[[d'Wort]] |date=4 April 2009 |accessdate=10 April 2009 }}</ref>

The party stands for increased pension rights,<ref name="Gegen Rentenklau" /> following on from Jaerling's former membership of the (formerly [[Single-issue politics|single-issue]]) [[Alternative Democratic Reform Party]]; [[social justice]]; and an [[anti-establishment]] opposition to the major political parties.<ref name="Gegen Rentenklau" />

