'''''The Slave's Cause''': A History of Abolition'' is a historical book by [[Manisha Sinha]]<ref name="RothmanTruth">{{cite news|last1=Rothman|first1=Adam|title=The Truth About Abolition|url=https://www.theatlantic.com/magazine/archive/2016/04/the-truth-about-abolition/471483/|accessdate=17 March 2016|publisher=The Atlantic|date=April 2016}}</ref><ref name="Donoghue">{{cite news|last1=Donoghue|first1=Steve|title='The Slave's Cause' is a thorough and overdue account of the abolition movement in the US|url=http://www.csmonitor.com/Books/Book-Reviews/2016/0216/The-Slave-s-Cause-is-a-thorough-and-overdue-account-of-the-abolition-movement-in-the-US|accessdate=17 March 2016|publisher=Christian Science Monitor|date=16 February 2016}}</ref><ref name="Price">{{cite news|last1=Price|first1=Matthew|title=Putting blacks at the center of abolitionism in ‘The Slave’s Cause’|url=https://www.bostonglobe.com/arts/books/2016/02/20/putting-blacks-not-liberal-whites-center-abolitionism/oO1Vpy2VxagQ3p2al4ubyH/story.html|accessdate=17 March 2016|publisher=Boston Globe|date=29 February 2016}}</ref> that was released in February 2016 by [[Yale University Press]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2016/02/28/books/review/the-slaves-cause-a-history-of-abolition-by-manisha-sinha.html|title=‘The Slave’s Cause: A History of Abolition,’ by Manisha Sinha|author=|date=28 February 2016|work=The New York Times}}</ref>
Writing in ''[[The Atlantic]]'', Adam Rothman calls ''The Slave's Cause'' "a stunning new history of [[abolitionism]]."<ref name="RothmanTruth"/>
